OVERVIEW OF POSITION
Graphic Designer is responsible for conceptualization and implement of design of solutions that meet marketing strategies from concept to completion. This position requires specialized knowledge of methods and techniques of graphic design and layout.
JOB DISCRIPTION
Essential Duties and Responsibilities include the following:
• Designing all marketing collaterals for Marketing & Sales Department based on sales & marketing plan;
• Developing concepts, graphics and layouts for product illustrations, company logos, and websites;
• Proposing new ideas and concepts;
• Liaising with suppliers to determine their requirements in term of graphic element;
• Managing to design & control print and production quality;
• Determining size and arrangement of illustrative material and copy, and font style and size;
• Preparing rough drafts of material based on an agreed brief;
• Reviewing final layouts and suggesting improvements if required;
• Liaising with external printers on a regular basis to ensure deadlines are met and material is printed to the highest quality;
• Be participating in events if required;
• Propose new ideas and concepts for the marketing/sales events and other activities to promote the brand awareness of the project;
• Controlling all event designs & mkt collaterals accordingly.
• Other duties may be assigned.

