Job Description:
Reports To
The Production Supervisor will report to Production section manager.
Job Overview
Manage production steps process, optimizing the performance of equipment and processes. Guide and train production operators in accordance to the company's competences, values and strategic plan.
Responsibilities and Duties
• Manage goals and results (by controls and reports). To break down the goals by sector, following and justifying the result of these in their area of activity;
• Study, coordinate and monitor improvements and / or new projects;
• Manage Human Resources (lead teams, work plans, vacations, leaves, layoffs, hiring, maintain discipline and order in sectors, movements, etc.);
• Record, analyze and complete any and all changes in process conditions and / or equipment in the area where you are working;
• Develop and give technical or operational training, focused on the productive area;
• Coordinate the update of procedures and work instructions;
• Assist on product formulas update;
• Be responsible for testing products and equipment, being responsible for the procedure, data recording, information and reports;
• Schedule and monitor preventive maintenance;
• Control, monitor and improve quality programs;

